article.headline: Cincinnati 67, Tennessee-Martin 49
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- John Williamson scored 23 points to lead Cincinnati to a 67-49 victory over Tennessee-Martin on Saturday night in the Jim Thorpe Classic, an exempted round-robin tournament. High Point beat Howard 81-62 in the late game. Marcus Sikes, who turned 22 on Saturday, had 18 points and 10 rebounds for Cincinnati (2-0). Bubba Tolliver led Tennessee-Martin (1-1) with 12 points, and Gerald Robinson had 10. Cincinnati built an early lead on 3-pointers, including two by Sikes, to jump out 13-2. Later in the half, consecutive 3-pointers by Williamson and a layup by Deonta Vaughn gave the Bearcats a 32-8 lead. Tennessee-Martin shot just 23 percent from the field, going 0-for-9 from 3-point range in the first half, and Cincinnati led 36-15 at halftime. Justin Flatt connected on a 3-point shot to bring the Skyhawks within 12 points at 54-42 with less than six minutes left to play, but they couldn't get closer. Cincinnati's quickness resulted in nine steals and 16 turnovers by Tennessee-Martin.
